OL,3,CGovernment introduces law to clear
OL,4,Cvictims of Post Office scandal
OL,6,FPostal Minister Kevin Hollinrake said
OL,7,Fthe current process to overturn
OL,8,Fconvictions was "taking too long", so
OL,9,Fthe government made the
OL,10,F"unprecedented" decision "of stepping
OL,11,Fin and legislating in this way to make
OL,12,Fsure we can both quash their
OL,13,Fconvictions and pay compensation
OL,14,Fquickly".
OL,16,FMr Hollinrake admitted there is a risk
OL,17,Fwith this legislation that some people
OL,18,Fwho aren't innocent could be
OL,19,Fexonerated - "this is the least worst
OL,20,Foption", he said.
