OL,3,CGovernment introduces law to clear
OL,4,Cvictims of Post Office scandal
OL,6,FThe government hopes the Bill will
OL,7,Freceive royal assent and become law
OL,8,Fahead of MPs' summer holiday.
OL,10,FBusiness Secretary Kemi Badenoch said
OL,11,Fministers "won't rest until every
OL,12,Fvictim receives the compensation they
OL,13,Fare entitled to".
OL,15,F"It is absolutely right that we sweep
OL,16,Faway the convictions wrongly given to
OL,17,Fpostmasters on the basis of bad
OL,18,Fevidence, and it is a disgrace that
OL,19,Fthey were ever pursued by the Post
OL,20,FOffice," she said.
